%N A393099 Number of 4-stack polyominoes having semiperimeter equal to n.
%C A393099 A convex polyomino is called a 4-stack if it can be decomposed into a central rectangle, with four (possibly empty) stack polyominoes placed on each side of the rectangle. Polyominoes are considered up to translation only; rotations and reflections are counted as distinct. The class of 4-stack polyominoes lies between L-convex (A126764) and Z-convex polyominoes (A128611) in the hierarchy of convex polyomino classes.
%H A393099 J.M. Fedou, A. Frosini, and Simone Rinaldi, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.tcs.2011.09.031">Enumeration of 4-stack polyominoes</a>, Theor. Comp. Sci. 502 (2013) 88-97.
%F A393099 G.f.: x^2 * (1-3*x)^2 / ((1-2*x) * (1-4*x)^(3/2)).
%F A393099 a(n) ~ sqrt(n) * 2^(2*n-6) / sqrt(Pi).
%e A393099 For semiperimeter 2,3,4,5 every convex polyomino (A005436) is 4-stack. For semiperimeter 6 we have 4 convex polyominoes which are not 4-stacks, precisely the 4 rotations of
